  "conclusions": [
    "For the natural prompt suite, DRAFT_MAX=2 was best: weighted decode 25.21 -> 40.17 tok/s, 1.593x, draft acceptance 0.745.",
    "Increasing DRAFT_MAX to 4 or 6 reduced acceptance enough to reduce throughput to 1.459x and 1.245x respectively.",
    "KV cache quantization did not improve absolute single-stream throughput: f16/f16 remained best at 40.04 tok/s MTP weighted decode.",
    "On repeated-token 512/128 and 4096/128 prompts, llama.cpp MTP reached 1.000 draft acceptance and about 48 tok/s decode; this is an artificial easy case, not a natural prompt estimate.",
    "hipEngine PARO eager decode beat llama.cpp server base on the repeated-token shape, but llama.cpp MTP remained faster when draft acceptance was perfect."
  ],
